          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "9Be(18O,13B). A 23-MeV/nucleon 13B secondary beam",
                " was produced from a 58-MeV/nucleon 18O primary beam",
                " impinging on a 3.8-mm-thick 9Be target. The secondary",
                " beam purity and intensity were 98% and about 2.0E4",
                " particles per second, respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A 6.76-mg/cm2 polyethylene target (CH2)n"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " TOF provided by two plastic scintillation",
                " detectors"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PPAC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two position-sensitive parallel plate",
                " avalanche chambers (PPACs) were employed to track the",
                " 13B beam before the physical target. The position",
                " resolution of two PPACs was about 1.5 mm [full width",
                " at half maximum (FWHM)]"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SISD",
                "SI",
                "CSICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Four sets of charged-particle",
                " telescopes (T0, T1, T2, TA) were employed in the",
                " large scattering chamber. T0, consisting of a double-",
                " sided silicon strip (DSSD) detector with a thickness",
                " of 1000 um, two large size silicon detectors (SSDs),",
                " and a layer of 4-cm-thick CsI(Tl) crystals. T1, same",
                " as T2, was composed of a 60-mm-thick DSSD, a SSD and",
                " an array of 4-cm-thick CsI(Tl) crystals. TA is a set",
                " of the annular double-sided silicon strip detector",
                " composed of six sectors."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF",
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The secondary beam was identified by the",
                " time of flight."
              ]
            }
